ive"" said Kranthi Bathini of Wealthmills. Also Read|Sensex, Nifty fall 1%, dragged by IT heavyweights; investors cautious ahead of Fed outcome Technical view & Trading strategy ""We are of the view that the current market texture is weak but oversold hence we could expect one quick pullback rally from the current levels. For the day traders now, 21,900 and 72,300 would act as key resistance zones for Nifty and Sensex, respectively,"" said Shrikant Chouhan of Kotak Securities. Below the same, the correction wave is likely to continue till 21,700-21,625 and 71,500-71,400, respectively. On the flip side, above 21,900 and 72,300 levels, the market could bounce back till 22000-22050 and 72500-72600 levels, Chouhan said, adding that the current market texture is volatile, hence level based trading would be the ideal strategy for the day-traders. Analysts expect investors to avoid both panic selling or fresh buying at the moment. ""Investors should wait for the quarterly results which will give the outlook for FY25. Elections are also coming up. We are in a wait-and-watch situation,"" said Amish Shah, Research analyst, Taurus Corporate Advisory Services. The sentiment was echoed by Shailesh Saraf of Value Stocks.
