 cash flow (FCF) of GBP 600-700 million in the last quarter, which should help them reduce their net debt to less than GBP 1 billion. At 9.20 am, the stock was trading at Rs 1,029 on the National Stock Exchange, up 1.6 percent from the previous close. Tata Motors' stock has rallied over 28 percent in the last three months.
