tion in the mortgage finance business, the company's ability to maintain its net interest margin while improving its operating efficiency and controlling the credit costs will be important from a credit perspective, it said. Also Read |Infy trades higher as Morgan Stanley retains 'overweight' call, awaits FY25 revenue guidance At 9:32am, PNB Housing Finance shares were trading 8 percent higher at Rs 682.00 on the National Stock Exchange (NSE). In the last one year, the stock has rallied more than 50 percent, outperforming Nifty 50 which has risen around 30 percent during this period.
